author: Stephanie Gleason
title: Dex Media Skips Interest Payment as Lenders Organize
text:
Dex Media Inc. has skipped an interest payment on more than $260 million in bond debt due Wednesday as its senior lenders organize to discuss a restructuring.
The yellow-pages company, the product of a merger through the twin bankruptcy cases of SuperMedia and Dex One, has until Oct. 30 to make the payment on the bonds before it becomes a default, according to a regulatory filing Wednesday.
